  "text": "The envoyproxy/envoy repository implements xDS API handling through a multi-layered architecture supporting both v2 and v3 protocols. The v2 xDS API is deprecated and no longer supported as of version 1.31.2, with the `checkTransportVersion()` function in source/common/config/utility.h explicitly rejecting V2 API versions and only allowing V3 or AUTO.\n\n## Core gRPC Mux Implementations\n\nThe gRPC-based xDS subscription mechanism is implemented in three main variants:\n\n1. **Legacy Implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc)**: The original GrpcMuxImpl class handles both state-of-the-world and delta-style xDS subscriptions. It manages bidirectional gRPC streams with v3::DiscoveryRequest and v3::DiscoveryResponse messages. The class maintains API state per resource type, handles request/response queueing, pause/resume logic, and TTL management.\n\n2. **Newer Delta Implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h/cc)**: The NewGrpcMuxImpl class specializes in delta xDS protocol, using v3::DeltaDiscoveryRequest and v3::DeltaDiscoveryResponse. It implements more efficient incremental resource updates and on-demand resource requests.\n\n3. **Unified Template-Based Implementation (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc)**: The newest architecture provides a generic GrpcMuxImpl template that works with both SotwSubscriptionState and DeltaSubscriptionState, supporting both v3::DiscoveryRequest/Response and v3::DeltaDiscoveryRequest/Response pairs. This includes specialized classes GrpcMuxSotw and GrpcMuxDelta.\n\n## Subscription State Management\n\nResource subscription state is tracked through:\n\n- **source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h/cc**: Implements state-of-the-world xDS semantics where the entire resource state is sent on each update. It maintains version_info and nonce tracking for ACK/NACK protocol.\n\n- **source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h/cc**: Implements delta xDS semantics where only resource changes are transmitted. Tracks per-resource versions and maintains requested/wildcard/ambiguous resource state maps.\n\n- **source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/delta_subscription_state.h/cc**: Legacy delta subscription state implementation for the older mux architecture.\n\n## gRPC Stream Transport\n\nThe **source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h** template class provides the low-level bidirectional gRPC stream management. It handles stream establishment, message serialization/deserialization, rate limiting, and retry logic for v3 proto messages. The stream callbacks trigger discovery response processing in the parent mux.\n\n## API Version Enforcement\n\nThe **source/common/config/utility.h** contains the critical `checkTransportVersion()` template method that validates the transport_api_version field in ApiConfigSource. This function explicitly rejects V2 API versions and logs deprecation warnings, ensuring all subscriptions use only V3 transport protocol.\n\n## Factory and Integration Points\n\n1. **source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.cc**: Implements ConfigSubscriptionFactory to instantiate appropriate mux implementations (GrpcMuxImpl, NewGrpcMuxImpl, or XdsMux variants) based on runtime feature flags and configuration.\n\n2. **source/common/config/subscription_factory_impl.h/cc**: The main subscription factory that orchestrates creation of file, REST, gRPC, or delta gRPC subscriptions, with API version validation via checkTransportVersion().\n\n3. **source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_context.h**: Contains the GrpcMuxContext structure that bundles configuration needed for all mux variants including async clients, dispatchers, service methods, and resource delegates.\n\n## Protocol Message Flow\n\nThe dual-version subscription handling follows this chain:\n1. SubscriptionFactoryImpl::subscriptionFromConfigSource validates transport_api_version (V3 only)\n2. GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory::create instantiates the appropriate mux with v3 proto types\n3. GrpcMuxImpl::addWatch queues DiscoveryRequest messages with v3 proto fields (version_info, response_nonce, resource_names)\n4. GrpcStream::sendMessage transmits v3 proto messages via gRPC\n5. GrpcMuxImpl::onDiscoveryResponse processes v3::DiscoveryResponse with nonce/version_info fields\n6. SotwSubscriptionState/DeltaSubscriptionState generate next requests using v3 proto API\n\nThe ADS (Aggregated Discovery Service) gRPC server subscribes to these mux implementations to receive resource updates across all types in a unified v3 proto stream."
}

